President Barack Obama will be delivering his third annual Back-to-School Speech at Benjamin Banneker Academic High School in Washington, DC on September 28, 2011. The speech is an opportunity for the President to directly address students and encourage them to study hard, take responsibility for their education, and set goals for themselves. Benjamin Banneker Academic High School is a magnet school that prepares students in grades 9-12 for college, and it has been recognized for its high graduation rates, college matriculation rates, and test scores. The speech will be live streamed on WhiteHouse.gov and can also be watched on MSNBC as part of NBC News' "Education Nation" programming.